---

Feature-level data for each object can be found in the data/ directory.
The logs of user and robot utterances and guesses (pointing) can be found in subjects/testing

---

run with

$ rosrun perception_classifiers fetch_features
$ rosrun perception_classifiers classifier_services

---

for robot, also run for TTS
$ rosrun sound_play soundplay_node.py

then start the game by calling ispy.py
$ rosrun perception_classifiers ispy.py [object_IDs] [num_rounds] \
  src/perception_classifiers/src/stopwords_en.txt [user_id/None] robot

---

Testing the dialog agent -

roscore

rosrun perception_classifiers python_classifier_services.py \
    --source_dir=/u/aish/Documents/Research/Code/catkin_ws/src/perception_classifiers/source_dir \
    --classifier_dir=/u/aish/Documents/Research/Code/catkin_ws/src/perception_classifiers/classifier_dir

rosrun perception_classifiers test_inquisitive_agent.py \
    --table_1_oidxs 0,1,2,3 \
    --table_2_oidxs 4,5,6,7 \
    --table_3_oidxs 8,9,10,11 \
    --io_type std \
    --logfn /u/aish/Documents/Research/Code/catkin_ws/src/perception_classifiers/log/trial.txt \
    --stopwords_fn /u/aish/Documents/Research/Code/catkin_ws/src/perception_classifiers/src/stopwords_en.txt \
    --initial_predicates_fn /u/aish/Documents/Research/Code/catkin_ws/src/perception_classifiers/source_dir/predicates.pickle \
    --policy_type example

